The origin, or proximal attachment, of the extensor pollicis brevis muscle is on the posterior surface of the distal radius, as well as along the distal interosseous membrane between the radius and ulna. The insertion, or distal attachment, is located at the base of the proximal phalanx of the thumb, or digit one.
